<http://dx.doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3609.2.9>
    bibo:endPage "238" ;
    bibo:issue "2" ;
    bibo:journal "Zootaxa" ;
    bibo:startPage "231" ;
    bibo:volume "3609" ;
    dc:creator "Koeda, Keita; Yoshino, Tetsuo; Tachihara, Katsunori" ;
    dc:date "2013" ;
    dc:title "Pempheris ufuagari sp. nov., a new species in the genus Pempheris (Perciformes, Pempheridae) from the oceanic islands of Japan" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.217288>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.217289> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.217288>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Two species of Pempheris collected from Kameike port, Minami Daito Island, Okinawa Pref., Japan. Both specimens collected by night-time angling. a: holotype of Pempheris ufuagari (NSMT-P 108633), 168.7 mm SL; b: P. oualensis (URM-P 46320), 183.0 mm SL." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/217288/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.217289>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Illustrations of scales of Pempheris species. a: P. ufuagari (URM-P 46323) which has weakly ctenoid, deciduous, thin, semicircular in shape, far wider than long scales; b: P. japonica (URM-P 45422) which has strongly ctenoid, adherent, divided into basal and distal halves scales. 1: scales from dorsal side; 2: scale from ventral side; 3: pored lateral-line scales. Each scale bar indicates 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/217289/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

